## ğŸ”· Step 5: Use Midpoint Formula

Since mirror line is perpendicular bisector:

M is midpoint of AH

Midpoint formula:

M = ((xâ‚ + xâ‚‚)/2 , (yâ‚ + yâ‚‚)/2)

So:

(4,4) = ((3 + x_H)/2 , (5 + y_H)/2)

Solve:

(3 + x_H)/2 = 4 â†’ x_H = 5  
(5 + y_H)/2 = 4 â†’ y_H = 3  

Final reflected point:

H = (5,3)

âœ” Proven

